Disease Description: when the upper teeth do not align with the lower teeth.
when the teeth are poorly positioned due to an excessively large measurement of some pieces or a bone that is too small.
The teeth are separated due to teeth that are too small or a bone that is too large.
when the crowns of the upper teeth exceed those of the lower teeth by more than a third.
when the front teeth do not touch each other.
when when biting and laterally the upper teeth close inside the lower ones.
the lower teeth are too forward.
The lower teeth close too far back.
